The paper discusses detecting feature interactions in highly-configurable systems, which is a topic related to software engineering (cs.SE). The approach proposed in the paper involves statically analyzing the source code of the system, which is a technique commonly used in programming languages research (cs.PL) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses using machine learning techniques for performance prediction, which is a topic related to systems engineering (cs.SY) and machine learning (cs.LG).
